  <div class="topic">
    <h4>Step 1: 12 Columns</h4>
    <p>If we think back to our Secret Tel Aviv project, we built a series of columns and rows. We'll define these columns and rows with CSS classes, and then to use them, we'll just give any ole' div these classes. The first class we'll define is <strong>col-1</strong>, which is "one column".</p>

    <p>If our grid is 12 columns, how wide is 1 column? You might need a calculator for this one:</p>

    <div class="exercise">
      <% var num= '5-2'; %>
      <div class="answer" ng-class="{'show': questions[<%= num %>]}">
        <p>8.33333333%; We just divide 100% by 12.</p>
      </div>

      <% include ../partials/answer-button %>
    </div>

    <p class="ex">Great. Now in your <strong>shoestrap.css</strong> file add:</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#9b703f">.col-1</span> {
  <span style="color:#c5af75">float</span>: <span style="color:#f9ee98">left</span>;
  <span style="color:#c5af75">width</span>: <span style="color:#dd7b3b">8.33333333<span style="color:#e28964">%</span></span>;
}
</pre>

    <p>And so we can actually see the columns, add the following in your <strong>style.css</strong> file:</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#cda869">div</span> {
  <span style="color:#c5af75">height</span>: <span style="color:#dd7b3b">50<span style="color:#e28964">px</span></span>;
  <span style="color:#c5af75">border</span>: <span style="color:#dd7b3b">1<span style="color:#e28964">px</span></span> <span style="color:#f9ee98">solid</span> <span style="color:#cf6a4c">red</span>;
}
</pre>

