  <div class="topic">
    <h4>Git Ignore</h4>
    <p>If we were going to put this "framework" on github for millions to use, we wouldn't want to include our <strong>index.html</strong> or <strong>style.css</strong> files because they're not curcial to our framework. To avoid pushing these to github, we can create a file called <strong>.gitignore</strong>. Do that now inside of your <strong>shoestrap</strong> folder.</p>

    <p>To tell git which files to ignore, we just add them on a new line at the top of our <strong>.gitignore</strong> file like this:</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8">index.html
style.css
</pre>

    <p>Now to remove them from git (becuase you likely already added them), type:</p>
    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8">git rm index.html
git rm style.css
</pre>

    <p>Then do a commit and push like normal!</p>
